# Two-base-rule flip feeding a downstream stratum: the NetAdded-refinement
# discriminator (T2). p has two base rules keyed on src's Which column; the
# same-batch flip -src(1,5)/+src(2,5) leaves p(5)'s presence unchanged. The
# downstream q(X) : p(X), r(X) must keep q(5) exactly once (no spurious
# re-derivation from a leaked net_additions frontier).
# Truth: after seed q={5}; after flip q={5}.
batch
+ r 5
+ src 1 5
end
batch
- src 1 5
+ src 2 5
end
